HEADWORD: Digladiate
<hw>Di*gla"di*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>digladiari</ets>; <ets>di- = dis-</ets> + <ets>gladius</ets> a
sword.]</ety> <def>To fight like gladiators; to contend fiercely; to
dispute violently.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Digladiating</qex> like ⟦AE⟧schines and Demosthenes.</q>
<rj><qau>Hales.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Digladiation</ent>⟦br⟧
